President Biden convened the inaugural meeting of the White House Council on Supply Chain Resilience as part of his Bidenomics agenda to lower costs for American families. He announced over 30 new actions to strengthen America's supply chains, including supporting domestic manufacturing of essential medicines and collaborating on data to identify supply chain risks. The President emphasized the need to keep supply chains secure, diversified, and resilient. Secretary Buttigieg also highlighted investments in supply chain infrastructure and efforts to improve working conditions for truck drivers. The Council members discussed these announcements and the importance of resilient supply chains to economic and national security. They also emphasized the economic benefits of investing in America and the fight against climate change. The meeting included participation from various agencies and highlighted the need for collaboration with the private sector.